main event: An unidentified flying object was sighted resembling a star with a light blue tinge in San Jose, California on 28 September 1964.
interesting points: The object was observed at a stationary elevation and did not twinkle., The observation was made at approximately 60 to 70 degrees altitude from the horizon., The source of the sighting was reported as military and is considered reliable., An error in the elevation recorded was noted, which should have been 45 degrees., There is a discrepancy regarding the time of observation which was listed as insufficient data.
sighted object: An object resembling a star with a light blue tinge
